data.title: Classic Dive Diner
data.text:
Complete with the irascible owner on premises and characters from the street good bad and indifferent.
However they are serving very good food at reasonable prices.

data.title: You can't go wrong if your coin is low and belly empty, you'll leave with change in your pocket and a full tummy
data.text: Long-long-long time Rochester eatery, basic "grub" served quick, cheap and with "atmosphere". In downtown, I'n our opinion, 3rd in line behind the Busy Bee and the king of all "eateries" Nick Tahou's

data.title: Do Not Overlook a Red Front Breakfast
data.text:
Love Trip Advisor.
Write a lovely review but I need a picture.
Presto Trip Advisor turns it into a draft that
has none of my draft in it ... if you know the
experience. Re-boot ... or rather re-write. 
My draft talks about a Buddy Rochester advised
Buddy breakfast. Moreover a request for a greasy
breakfast was more than satisfied with pay up front
friendly old time service with lots to look at ...

... do not overlook a Red Front classic Breakfast.
